  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nNessDan in discord pointed out that or VC doesn't work with with Teku's BN. It's because we have an additional `is_syncing` field in the `/node/syncing` endpoint response.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nv1.0.6\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\nConnected to beacon node endpoint: http://localhost:5051/, version: teku/v20.12.1/linux-x86_64/-ubuntu-openjdk64bitservervm-java-11\r\nUnable connect to beacon node error: Reqwest(reqwest::Error { kind: Decode, source: Error(\"missing field `is_syncing`\", line: 1, column: 50) })\r\nConnected to beacon node endpoint: http://localhost:5051/, version: teku/v20.12.1/linux-x86_64/-ubuntu-openjdk64bitservervm-java-11\r\nUnable connect to beacon node error: Reqwest(reqwest::Error { kind: Decode, source: Error(\"missing field `is_syncing`\", line: 1, column: 50) })\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nVC compatible with teku.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nBecause the `/node/syncing` endpoint returns with a sync distance of 1 when we receive a block and are processing it, it might be better to use the `/node/health` endpoint and base this check on the 200 status code. I'll look into what other clients are doing.",
